benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Remove tags from payment

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios are covered (TC01-TC04) for removing all or specific tags from a payment.
Handling of special cases such as no tags present (TC05) and tag absence on payment (TC10).
Input validation scenarios are covered (TC06 invalid paymentId format, TC09 invalid tagDef value).
Missing header scenario covered (TC08), and unauthorized access (TC11).
System error handling covered (TC12) and timeout scenario (TC22).
Edge cases with extra parameters (TC14) and large numbers of tagDef parameters (TC15).
Audit logging integration (TC20) and data consistency verification via subsequent GET (TC21).
Non-existent paymentId test (TC07) and tag-not-present-on-payment test (TC10).
Varied deletion scenarios including single/multiple tagDefs (TC02, TC03).
gaps: 403 Forbidden scenario (insufficient permissions) not explicitly tested beyond 401 (TC11).
Rate limiting / throttling behavior not tested.
Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) for DELETE responses not tested.
Idempotence deeper validation across repeated deletions (beyond TC01) could be strengthened.
Pagination tests are not applicable to DELETE but GET listing of tags/pagination for related data is not covered by this suite.
recommendations: Add a dedicated test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions beyond the 401 unauthorized case.
Introduce rate-limiting tests (e.g., multiple rapid DELETE requests) to validate resilience under load.
Validate caching headers on DELETE responses (ETag/Cache-Control) if applicable in the API contract.
Enhance idempotence verification by performing repeated DELETE requests and asserting stable final state.
If applicable, add GET/list pagination tests to cover large datasets outside the DELETE path, ensuring end-to-end data handling remains consistent.
